    "image_with_text_667ak4": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_rBTbbM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h4>Chemical contamination</h4><p>Heavy use of fertilizers, pesticides and insecticides is a major cause of water contamination and decreased soil fertility. The toxicity of such products is also a threat to biodiversity.</p>",
            "description_size": "medium",
            "font_size": 16,
            "font_weight": 300
          }
        },
        "text_YqXLAD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h4>Soil depletion</h4><p>Lack of soil rotation and the use of synthetic fertilizers, pesticides and GMO seeds cause soil depletion in cotton farming. This includes soil degradation and erosion, as well as loss of soil fertility and biodiversity.</p>",
            "description_size": "medium",
            "font_size": 16,
            "font_weight": 300
          }
        },
        "text_d334PM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h4>Water scarcity</h4><p>Inefficient irrigation systems combined with degraded soil that have low water absorbency are the main reasons why water is overused in cotton farming and causing water scarcity. </p>",
            "description_size": "medium",
            "font_size": 16,
            "font_weight": 300
          }
        }
      },
